Remove pyrefly suppression comments between @_overload_method and def

openRuyi ships CPython 3.13.8, whose inspect.getsourcelines() truncates
the extracted source of a decorated function when a comment-only line
sits between the last decorator and the def (inspect.BlockFinder handles
tokenize.NEWLINE too strictly; fixed upstream in later 3.13.x):
  https://github.com/python/cpython/issues/139783

TorchScript parses the source of every @torch._jit_internal._overload_method
stub at import time (_check_overload_body -> torch._sources.parse_def), so
the three RNN/LSTM/GRU forward stubs in torch/nn/modules/rnn.py that carry a
"# pyrefly: ignore [bad-override]" line in that position make any
"import torch" fail with:
  IndentationError: expected an indented block after function definition

Dropping the three comment lines is behavior-neutral: pyrefly is a static
type checker never run in the distro build.

diff --git a/torch/nn/modules/rnn.py b/torch/nn/modules/rnn.py
index 76bfa4e..7bdbe4d 100644
--- a/torch/nn/modules/rnn.py
+++ b/torch/nn/modules/rnn.py
@@ -655,7 +655,6 @@ class RNN(RNNBase):
 
     @overload
     @torch._jit_internal._overload_method  # noqa: F811
-    # pyrefly: ignore [bad-override]
     def forward(
         self,
         input: Tensor,
@@ -1063,7 +1062,6 @@ class LSTM(RNNBase):
     # Same as above, see torch/nn/modules/module.py::_forward_unimplemented
     @overload  # type: ignore[override]
     @torch._jit_internal._overload_method  # noqa: F811
-    # pyrefly: ignore [bad-override]
     def forward(
         self,
         input: Tensor,
@@ -1365,7 +1363,6 @@ class GRU(RNNBase):
 
     @overload  # type: ignore[override]
     @torch._jit_internal._overload_method  # noqa: F811
-    # pyrefly: ignore [bad-override]
     def forward(
         self,
         input: Tensor,
